  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Project Requirements**\n\nOkay, I\'m diving into the project brief and visual assets for the Romanian application. I\'m focusing on dissecting the feature set and user interface elements. This includes determining the data models needed for each screen and the core functionality, as well as the layout and user experience, while keeping the specific company\'s vision in mind.\n\n\n**Defining Landing Page Elements**\n\nI\'ve moved on to the design for the Romanian application\'s landing page (Acas\304\203). I\'m focusing on the structural elements. This involves a clear header with logo and navigation, a hero section with specific wording and a striking visual, and a trust section. I\'m taking a close look at the provided image link for the hero section\'s card and considering how to best represent the \"SISTEM ACTIV Protec\310\233ie \303\256n timp real 24/7\" badge and its shield icon.\n\n\n**Developing Bento-Style Content**\n\nI\'m now detailing the Bento box section for the Acas\304\203 page of the Romanian app. I\'m focusing on \"Oferim solu\310\233ii complete de securitate\" content. I am breaking it into modular sections: \"Montaj profesionist,\" \"Acces mobil,\" \"Service & mentenan\310\233\304\203,\" and an upgrade banner. I\'m also planning the CTA, text and buttons (\"Contact WhatsApp\" and \"Trimite Email\"), and the footer elements, including the logo, links (terms, policy), and location details.\n\n\n**Designing Quote Form**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the \"Solicit\304\203 Ofert\304\203\" screen\'s design. I\'m prioritizing the left side with its content: the header \"Securitate Inteligent\304\203\" and the custom image of the camera in Bucovina, along with the \"Tehnologie de ultim\304\203 or\304\203 \303\256n Bucovina\" badge and the two cards for rapid response and technical support. Currently, I\'m working to arrange the form fields on the right side, including name, phone, and email, while simultaneously working on the other fields. I\'m focusing on user flow and making the form responsive.\n\n\n**Formulating Input Field Specifications**\n\nI\'m now nailing down the specifics of the quote form\'s input fields. I\'m focusing on the \"Solicit\304\203 Ofert\304\203\" form. I\'m structuring \"Localitate\" as a text input, followed by a location type dropdown, and a new/upgrade system dropdown. I\'ll include a number of cameras slider. I\'m adding an optional message textarea and a GDPR checkbox. Finally, I\'m integrating a \"Trimite cererea\" button with an arrow icon for submission. I also need to make it responsive.\n\n\n**Detailing Security System Components**\n\nI\'m now detailing the security system components. I am designing a minimalist system with a high-fidelity built-in microphone. I\'m focusing on exterior cameras (IP67, antivandal, ColorVu, including a specific image). I\'m specifying DVR/NVR units with secure storage and H.265+ support. I\'m also addressing phone access (live monitoring, P2P), cabling and configuration (aesthetic, optimized), and maintenance (lens cleaning, HDD checks), along with service and upgrade options (analog to UHD). I have the CTA section finalized, including the two options for offer request, and WhatsApp.\n\n\\n\\n\n\n**Organizing Portfolio Screen**\n\nI am now organizing the portfolio screen details (Portofoliu). I need to determine the best way to display the security system components that I had previously documented, while focusing on a layout that presents the offerings.\n\n\n**Structuring Portfolio Presentation**\n\nI\'m now detailing the \"Portofoliu\" screen. The hero text will be \"PORTOFOLIU. Solu\310\233ii de securitate \310\231i automatizare... Descoperi\310\233i modul \303\256n care transform\304\203m spa\310\233iile clien\310\233ilor no\310\231tri...\" I am working on case studies. I am currently planning project details for a residential property with a premium villa image and an industrial/warehouse project image.\n\n\n**Developing Portfolio Section**\n\nI\'m now detailing a \"Portofoliu\" screen section for commercial space with a boutique retail image. I\'ll include anti-theft and client traffic details. Then, I am going to plan another case study for a \"Pensiune / unitate turistic\304\203\" with a wooden pension image, focusing on tourism, automated check-in with smart locks, and CCTV functionality. After that, I will work on a screen with an active interactive tab for the CRM and admin dashboard.\n\n\n**Constructing CRM Panel**\n\nI\'m now designing the CRM/admin dashboard\'s core structure and data presentation. This will include key performance indicators (KPIs) like monthly requests, active projects, conversion rate, and average response time. I\'m visualizing a Kanban pipeline to track leads through stages such as \"New,\" \"Contacted,\" \"Scheduled,\" and \"Completed,\" complete with clickable client details. The client list table will be included, and I\'ll ensure full interactivity for updating lead status and details.\n\n\n**Integrating Lead Generation**\n\nI\'ve just added lead source integration to the CRM, where new quote requests from the multi-screen configurator automatically pop up in the \"New\" column. The user can easily move leads through the pipeline by dragging or clicking. I\'m also including a mechanism for directly adding custom leads. No need to over-engineer this. I am now exploring possible AI features.\n\n\n**Refining UI Element Integration**\n\nI\'m now focusing on integrating the specified logo image from the visual guide, double-checking the URL link for the portfolio view. I\'m prioritizing direct image links for the visual elements. I\'m also preparing for the interactive quote form and the CRM, focusing on responsiveness and user flow.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 21
      nanos: 246281764
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
